					type: "item"
				}
			]
			title: "Pipez"
			x: 6.0d
			y: -2.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["QL01000000000012"]
			description: ["Modular Routers handle routing logic that Pipez cannot: conditional dispatch, distance transfer, and player-side item delivery. A Router inspects each item passing through it and applies Module cards to determine where it goes. The Distributer Module round-robins items across multiple outputs. The Vacuum Module pulls items from the world around it. The Sender Module transmits items to a linked destination across any distance. The Player Module deposits items directly into a specific player's inventory. Use Modular Routers when simple pipe filters are insufficient — GTCEu multi-output centrifuge byproducts going to different drawers are a common case where routers pay for themselves immediately."]
			id: "QL01000000000013"
			rewards: [{
				count: 2
				id: "QL03000000000013"
				item: "mmorpg:currency/mirror"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "QL02000000000018"
				item: "modularrouters:modular_router"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "Modular Routers"
			x: 6.0d
			y: -4.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["QL01000000000001"]
			description: ["The Corpse mod creates a physical body at your death location that holds all your items and experience. The corpse persists in the world until you interact with it — right-click to retrieve everything at once. Corpses have a configurable despawn timer; by default they last long enough to return from any death point if you moved directly. The corpse key (default: none — open inventory while dead) shows a preview of what the corpse holds. Corpses do not lock or protect items from other players on multiplayer. Memorize your last coordinates on death or set a JourneyMap waypoint at your corpse before it disappears."]
			id: "QL01000000000014"
			rewards: [{
				count: 2
				id: "QL03000000000014"
				item: "mmorpg:currency/mirror"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "QL02000000000019"
				title: "Die and Recover Your Corpse"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			title: "Corpse"
			x: -3.0d
			y: -5.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["QL01000000000014"]
			description: ["Carry On lets you pick up any block that has an inventory or any non-boss mob by Shift+Right-clicking with an empty hand. The carried entity follows you and can be placed anywhere. Use this to relocate chests with contents intact, move passive mobs into farms without leads, reposition GTCEu machines without breaking and rebuilding them, or carry workbenches and crafting stations between locations. Blocks with active processes (machines mid-recipe, furnaces burning) will pause when picked up and resume when placed. The carry limit is one block or mob at a time; you cannot sprint or attack while carrying."]
			id: "QL01000000000015"
			rewards: [{
				count: 2
				id: "QL03000000000015"
				item: "mmorpg:currency/mirror"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "QL02000000000020"
				title: "Carry a Mob or Block"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			title: "Carry On"
			x: -3.0d
			y: -7.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["QL01000000000015"]
			description: ["Paragliders provide gliding from any elevated position. Craft a Paraglider and bind it to a Curios slot or hotbar. While airborne, hold Jump to deploy — the glider extends and slows your descent. You can glide indefinitely as long as you maintain forward momentum and altitude. Paragliders do not require fuel and do not break. They are the earliest free-flight analog in the pack before the Create Jetpack or Soul Land movement cultivation bonuses. Use them to safely descend from tall structures, cross canyons, and scout terrain from ridge lines before you have verticality from other systems."]
			id: "QL01000000000016"
			rewards: [{
				count: 2
				id: "QL03000000000016"
				item: "mmorpg:currency/mirror"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "QL02000000000021"
				item: "paragliders:paraglider"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "Paragliders"
			x: -3.0d
			y: -8.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["QL01000000000016"]
			description: ["The Create Jetpack provides powered vertical and directional flight using compressed air stored in the jetpack's internal tank. Fuel it by connecting to a Compressed Air Tank or by crafting with a charged tank directly. Press Space while airborne to ascend; the jetpack fires downward thrusters and maintains altitude. Higher-tier jetpacks use better materials and hold more air, extending flight time significantly. The Create Jetpack occupies the chest Curios slot, which competes with Sophisticated Backpacks — decide based on whether you need carry capacity or flight for a given session. Both cannot be equipped simultaneously."]
			id: "QL01000000000017"
			rewards: [{
				count: 3
				id: "QL03000000000017"
